[normal]&#xa0;[bold]An example of supplies of critical materials in the UK – Hemerdon, Devon[bold]Hemerdon is the fourth largest deposit of tungsten in the world.
[normal] It is an example of the new opportunities for the UK to provide secure supplies of critical and economically crucial minerals for our economy from within our own significant and undeveloped resources. Tungsten is important as it is an essential mineral fo
[normal]r use in cutting tools and for hardened steel. Currently almost 78% of the world’s production of Tungsten comes from China. The annual production from Hemerdon will provide around 4% of global demand, meet the demand from within the UK and contribute towar
[normal]ds exports
[normal]. 
[normal]The mine will employ around 250 people directly, with additional indirect employment.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Source: 
