[normal]National Engagement - T[bold]he[bold] UK Minerals Forum[bold].
[normal]6.2
[normal]              
[normal]The UK Minerals Forum was set by the CBI Minerals Group in 2006 because there was 
[normal]a perceived n
[normal]eed to draw together all key stakeholders, to debate and inform 
[normal]government and the public on the prudent use, sustainable management and 
[normal]supply of UK minerals. The UKMF has a broad membership drawn from industry, regulators, NGOs and government
[normal] who sit as observers
[normal]. It holds regular meetings and convenes working groups to research and report on critical issues. 
[normal]We believe the Forum is a goo
[normal]d example of best practice in engagement between all stakeholders who have an interest in the UK based extractive industry.
[normal]http://www.bgs.ac.uk/ukmf/home.html
[normal]&#xa0;
